Even if they look good, & there doesn't seem to be anything wrong with them, you don't know for sure, until you mount the scope, & try it.

However, we do guarantee, there is nothing obviously wrong with the scope, we don't tell you about.

I have well over a dozen Illuminators, just like this one.  All of them have been disassembled, & cleaned; & they work good.  All of these original Redfields, should be disassembled, & cleaned, before mounting them on a rifle.  This usually costs about $60.00.  You should figure that in, when buying the scope.

We have used several scope repair companies.  The two we would absolutely NOT recommend, to anyone; are:  Iron Sights, & ABO.

We have sent a couple Redfields to Iron Sights, & it took a year to get them back, & they still had the same problems, they had, when we sent them in.

ABO, is even worse.  They either can't, or won't, fix anything properly, & they do not stand behind their work.  They are very expensive; also.  We would not recommend you send a toy scope, or a Tasco (same thing actually), to ABO; much less a prized Redfield, such as an Illuminator.

That said; there are several other scope repair companies; which are reputable; who will disassemble, & clean a Redfield.

title: For Sale:  Noveske N4 AR-15 300AAC *New in Box* AR15
postcontent: The Noveske 300 AAC BLACKOUT is designed to run optimally firing both subsonic suppressed and supersonic unsuppressed. This barrel is tuned to lock back on the last round using subsonic 220 and 208 grain ammunition with a sound suppressor. The firearm may not lock back with subsonic 220 and 208 grain ammunition without a sound suppressor. This is a like new M&P 22 Compact that I bought in August '14 (test fire cartridge date 06/26/2014.  I've had it to the range four or five times, firing approximately 400 rounds total ammo count through the pistol.  It cycles Remington, CCI, Aquila, Federal & Winchester ammo perfectly.  I've only ever had issue with American Eagle red box stuff, but I'm not surprised because my 10/22 chokes on that junk too.

It's a great reliable 22LR semi-auto pistol, but I've become bored with it.  It's really accurate and includes 3 dot white adjustable sights (allen wrench included).  It also has a threaded barrel.  However S&W does not include a cap wrench with the pistol (like the full size M&P 22), so I've never had the thread protector cap off.  It also has an ambidextrous manual thumb safety, right handed but reversible magazine release switch, and an internal safety (keys included).

Included:
S&W M&P 22 Compact semi-auto pistol
Two 10-round steel magazines
Unopened box Winchester 22LR 40gr ammo (222 rounds)
Box, manual, sight allen wrench, keys, cable lock

I'm asking $250 cash, which is a great deal as Vance's currently sells new for $319.99 (on sale and without the ammo).  Email or text REDACTED
